default4. ActivitiesdefaultPPI – ME runs frequent, year-round programming, which includes the following:
defaultPeacePlayers Basketball Clubsdefault – A network of youth basketball clubs in which 
defaultPalestinians and Israelis
default children come together for integrated practices led the guidance of a diverse group of coaches.
defaultJerusalem All-Stars: defaultThree fully integrated PPI – ME team
defaults compete in the Israel Basketball Association’s elite youth league, in cooperation with top women's basketball club ASA Jerusalem. Teams are comprised of 
defaultIsraeli and Palestinian
default girls from East and West Jerusalem, marking the first time a joint 
defaultPalestinia
defaultn-Israeli
default team from Jerusalem has joined the league.
defaultPeace Education Retreats: defaultPalestinian and Israeli
default participants embark on one three-day retreat per year, at which they take part in intensive peace education workshops.
defaultLeadership Development Program: defaultEx
defaultceptional teen leaders engage in weekly practices, volunteer as assistant coaches with younger participants, lead social action projects and embark on an annual three-day Leadership Development Retreat.
defaultCoaches for Conflict Resolution:default defaultPPI – ME's newest pr
defaultogram, launched in 2013, Coaches for Conflict Resolution is
default a two-year bilingual (Arabic and Hebrew) training program, designed and implemented by PPI – ME in cooperation with Zinman College at the Wingate Institute and the Arbinger Institute. The course f
defaulteatures professional coaching certification training (legally required for coaching in Israel and East Jerusalem); quarterly intensive conflict resolution workshops (including an annual weekend retreat); foreign language instruction (Arabic for Israelis, H
defaultebrew for Palestinians) to enhance symmetry, instill an appreciation for the "other's" culture, and to improve participants' ability to communicate with one another;  and a year-long hands-on supervised practicum, in which coaches-in-training help facilita
defaultte joint activities for PPBC participants.
