default5. EvaluationsdefaultIndependent evaluators conduct impact evaluations on PPI 
default–
default ME's programs on an annual basis. From 2005 
default–
default 2011, evaluations were conducted by a group of researchers from Bar-Ilan University. Data demonstrated the both 
defaultPalestinian and Israeli
default participants had fewer stereotypes and ethnocentric attitudes and were more willing to engage in social contact with th
defaulte "other" side following participation in the program. These positive attitudes became stronger with long-term participation over the course of four years. 
defaultIn the 2012-2013 program year, PPI 
default–
default ME 
defaultlanched
default a long-term randomized control trial (RCT) conducte
defaultd by two professional evaluators, 
defaultin cooperation with
default New York Universit
defaulty
default. The s
defaulttudy will take place over three 
defaultyears, and will employ sophisticated behavioral and attitudinal measures to study the effects of PPI’s programs on adolescents living in conflic
defaultt, examining intergroup and intra-group perceptions, political identity formation, and communities’ capacities for conflict management. 
defaultIn 2013, the pilot year of the study was completed successfully, and conclusion
defaults
default from the pilot study were used to refin
defaulte the methodology. The second year of the study has recently been launched.
default Funding has been achieved for an additional two years of research, and the organization and the university are currently seeking funding in order to extend the study further.
default Littl
defaulte quantitative research exists in the field of grassroots peace-building interventions, and the results of the study will represent a much needed addition to the understanding of conflict resolution.
